  "title": "100 Monkeys Just Broke Out of Their Enclosure",
  "script": "A hundred monkeys broke out? In Lopburi, Thailand — the town that already worships its monkeys — nearly 100 macaques tore through their enclosure at the local nursery overnight. They didn't just wander off. They flooded the neighborhood, and at least one strolled straight into a police station like it owned the place, as rescue crews scrambled with tranquilizer darts and bait cages, working street by street to round them back up — and here's the part that should worry you: officials say they barely held back 1,000 more monkeys from following the first hundred out the door. Lopburi built a festival around feeding these guys. Now it's building a strategy to contain them. So what happens when the other 1,000 decide it's their turn?",
